HEADWORD: Masthead
<hw>Mast"head`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>The top or head of a mast; the part of a mast above the
hounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Masthead</ent>⟦br⟧

